  "description" : "Three years later, a boy named Chess Demon King emerged from the mountains. He was a disciple of the highly skilled chess player, the old Chess Demon King, and an extremely impulsive and uncouth youth. In the capital city, at the Tianxuan Chess Hall, the owner was a young girl named Xiaoyun, whose idol was Jiang Liuer, who had defeated the Japanese prodigy chess player, and who vowed to marry her someday. At the Tianxuan Chess Hall, Xiaoyun`s good friend Fang Baihua often played chess with other patrons. Chess Demon King was excited to see the hall and, upon entering, encountered Fang Baihua leaving. He immediately approached her, praising her beauty and calling her \"pretty sister.\" Xiaoyun agreed to let him stay temporarily at her hall, but only on odd jobs.\nAfter hearing about Jiang Liuer, Chess Demon King decided to go to Lingyun Temple to play a game of chess with him. The young monks, sensing his ill intentions, told him Jiang Liuer wasn`t there. Chess Demon King then left a chess score in the Buddhist hall and departed.\nAfter hearing about the old chess demon king from Master Yuande, Jiang Liuer decided to go to the capital to meet this young chess demon king. He stayed at the Tianxuan Chess Hall.\nsource: bgm.tv\\googletranslate",
